{"name": "django-interval", "metadata": {"name": "django-interval", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["django"], "summary": "A Django field for storing fuzzy date information", "upload_time": 1734006665}, "documentation": ["# Django Interval\n\ndjango-interval is a [Django](https://www.djangoproject.com/) app. It provides\nmodel fields to store date information with some extra data stored in\nadditional fields. The additional fields are composed of a `_sort`, a `_from`\nand a `_to` field that store data that is generated from the string stored in\nthe main model field.\n\n# Installation\n\nInstall `django-interval` and add `django_interval` to your\n[INSTALLED_APPS](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/stable/ref/settings/#std-setting-INSTALLED_APPS).\n\nUse either the `django_interval.fields.FuzzyDateParserField` or the\n`django_interval.fields.FuzzyDateRegexField` in your models. Both\ncome with sensible defaults (a parser method in the `FuzzyDateParserField`\nand a list of regexes in the `FuzzyDateRegexField`), but it is possible\nto pass custom parser or regexes as arguments.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "django_interval.fields", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "django_interval.fields.FROM_PATTERN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_interval.fields.TO_PATTERN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_interval.fields.SORT_PATTERN", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "django_interval.fields.GenericDateIntervalField", "bases": ["CharField"], "methods": [{"name": "django_interval.fields.GenericDateIntervalField.add_generated_date_field", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_interval.fields.GenericDateIntervalF